                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Governor <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>, of Louisiana.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-07-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Italian chargé requests report on alleged lynching at Tallulah of five Italians
                    and asks protection of any Italian subjects who may be <pb facs="0537" n="441"
                        xml:id="pg_441"/> in danger. Were persons lynched Italian subjects or
                    naturalized Americans?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
